
Setting Up a Skupper Network
===========================================================

We have two site directories: west and east.

Both directories contain a site.yaml file.

One directory contains a listener.yaml, and the other contains
a connector.yaml.

And both sites have a Helm Chart.

The User launches Helm twice, once for each namespace, with
commands something like this:

  helm install skupper oci://quay.io/skupper/helm/skupper \
    --namespace west \
    --create-namespace \
    --set scope=namespace

Helm then starts issuing commands that the User would have to
do manually, like "kubectl apply YAML_FILE"

When the API Server gets the YAML files applied, it creates a
Deployment in the desired Namespace.


The Kubelet on that Node pulls the image for the Container
(or Containers) of the Pod that is starting.

When those images start running, the container’s ENTRYPOINT 
with CMD runs the Go binary (the controller main function)

When the Controller starts running, it:

  * Loads the kubeconfig and creates clientsets

  * Sets up informers for the Skupper CRDs 
    (Site, Link, Listener, Connector, etc.). 

  * Starts the reconciliation loops

And now we're rolling!



